  "prompt": "I'm sick of hearing about Trump, can I block these questions on my Quora feed?",
  "response": "Yes, you can customize your Quora feed to block topics or questions that you find uninteresting, including those related to Trump. Here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. **Mute Topics**: If you see a question related to a topic you're not interested in, you can mute that topic by clicking on the three dots (More) under the question and selecting \"Mute Topic.\" This will help reduce the number of questions about that topic in your feed.\n\n2. **Adjust Feed Preferences**: You can also adjust your feed preferences to follow topics that interest you more and unfollow topics that don\u2019t. \n\n3. **Report or Feedback**: If there are specific questions or content that you find inappropriate or overly repetitive, you can provide feedback to Quora to improve your experience.\n\n4. **Personalization Settings**: Regularly check your personalization settings to refine what you see in your feed based on your interests.\n\nBy taking these steps, you should be able to minimize the content related to Trump in your Quora feed.",
